com.google.flightmap.common.db
Class CachedAirportDirectory

java.lang.Object
  com.google.flightmap.common.db.AbstractAirportDirectory
      com.google.flightmap.common.db.CachedAirportDirectory
All Implemented Interfaces:
AirportDirectory
public class CachedAirportDirectory
extends AbstractAirportDirectory

Caches access to AirportDirectory for improved performance.

Area searches are cached by retrieving all airports within a larger area than requested, and keeping the results in memory. Subsequent requests are served from memory, as long as the requested area is included in the cached area.

Requesting a search area that is not included in the cached area results in clearing the cache and starting all over. Results needed to build the cache are obtained by querying an underlying AirportDirectory.

The following figures illustrate this process.

A first area search is performed: a larger area is cached.

All subsequent area searches that fall within the cached area are served from memory.

When an area search falls outside of the cached area (cache miss), the latter is cleared.

A new cached area is then retrieved for the following requests.

Method Detail

getAirportsInRectangle

public Collection<Airport> getAirportsInRectangle(LatLngRect area,
                                                  int minRank)
                                           throws InterruptedException
Description copied from interface: AirportDirectory
Returns airports in area.

The returned collection is in fact a set: no airport can be included more than once. The return value is kept as a Collection for performance reasons: membership tests in Set implementations can be unecessarily costly.

Parameters:
area - Area of search
minRank - Minimum airport rank to return
Throws:
InterruptedException

isCacheMatch

public boolean isCacheMatch(LatLngRect area,
                            int minRank)
Returns true if area and minRank will either 1) hit the cache, or 2) give the same results as the query that's in progress by getAirportsInRectangle(LatLngRect, int).
